    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Acute onset, focal\nweakness\nof 1 or more extremity\nDecreased muscular tone\nAbsent or hypoactive\nreflexes\nRarely have\nnumbness\n, but may have some\nneuropathic pain\nFever\nand other symptoms of infection by causative virus (e.g.\nURI\nsymptoms,\ngastroenteritis\n)\nIn severe cases:\nBulbar dysfunction (\ndysphagia\n,\ndysarthria\n,\ndysphonia\n,\nfacial weakness\n, ptosis)\nRespiratory muscle weakness\nAutonomic instability,\narrhythmias\nif cervical lesion present\nParalysis usually maximal at 3-5 days after onset",
